  59. ‌void caml_raise(value v)
  60. {
  61.   Caml_check_caml_state();
  62.   char* exception_pointer;

  64.   Unlock_exn();

  66.   CAMLassert(!Is_exception_result(v));

  68.   // avoid calling caml_raise recursively
  69.   v = caml_process_pending_actions_with_root_exn(v);
  70.   if (Is_exception_result(v))
  71.     v = Extract_exception(v);

  73.   exception_pointer = (char*)Caml_state->c_stack;

  75.   if (exception_pointer == NULL) {
  76.     caml_terminate_signals();
  77.     caml_fatal_uncaught_exception(v);
  78.   }

  80.   while (Caml_state->local_roots != NULL &&
  81.          (char *) Caml_state->local_roots < exception_pointer) {
  82.     Caml_state->local_roots = Caml_state->local_roots->next;
  83.   }

  85.   caml_raise_exception(Caml_state, v);
  86. }

  96. ‌void caml_raise_with_arg(value tag, value arg)
  97. {
  98.   CAMLparam2 (tag, arg);
  99.   CAMLlocal1 (bucket);

  101.   bucket = caml_alloc_small (2, 0);
  102.   Field(bucket, 0) = tag;
  103.   Field(bucket, 1) = arg;
  104.   caml_raise(bucket);
  105.   CAMLnoreturn;
  106. }

  108. ‌void caml_raise_with_args(value tag, int nargs, value args[])
  109. {
  110.   CAMLparam1 (tag);
  111.   CAMLxparamN (args, nargs);
  112.   value bucket;
  113.   int i;

  115.   bucket = caml_alloc (1 + nargs, 0);
  116.   Field(bucket, 0) = tag;
  117.   for (i = 0; i < nargs; i++) Field(bucket, 1 + i) = args[i];
  118.   caml_raise(bucket);
  119.   CAMLnoreturn;
  120. }

  122. ‌void caml_raise_with_string(value tag, char const *msg)
  123. {
  124.   CAMLparam1(tag);
  125.   value v_msg = caml_copy_string(msg);

  188. ‌CAMLexport value caml_raise_if_exception(value res)
  189. {
  190.   if (Is_exception_result(res)) caml_raise(Extract_exception(res));
  191.   return res;
  192. }

  194. /* We use a pre-allocated exception because we can't
  195.    do a GC before the exception is raised (lack of stack descriptors
  196.    for the ccall to [caml_array_bound_error]).  */
  197. ‌static value array_bound_exn(void)
  198. {
  199.   static atomic_uintnat exn_cache = ATOMIC_UINTNAT_INIT(0);
  200.   const value* exn = (const value*)atomic_load_acquire(&exn_cache);
  201.   if (!exn) {
  202.     exn = caml_named_value("Pervasives.array_bound_error");
  203.     if (!exn) {
  204.       fprintf(stderr, "Fatal error: exception "
  205.         "Invalid_argument(\"index out of bounds\")\n");
  206.       exit(2);
  207.     }
  208.     atomic_store_release(&exn_cache, (uintnat)exn);
  209.   }
  210.   return *exn;
  211. }

  213. ‌void caml_array_bound_error(void)
  214. {
  215.   caml_raise(array_bound_exn());
  216. }

  218. ‌void caml_array_bound_error_asm(void)
  219. {
  220.   /* This exception is raised directly from ocamlopt-compiled OCaml,
  221.      not C, so we jump directly to the OCaml handler (and avoid GC) */
  222.   caml_raise_exception(Caml_state, array_bound_exn());
  223. }

  225. ‌int caml_is_special_exception(value exn) {
  226.   return exn == (value) caml_exn_Match_failure
  227.     || exn == (value) caml_exn_Assert_failure
  228.     || exn == (value) caml_exn_Undefined_recursive_module;
  229. }
